{
    "abstract": "This chapter describes a novel approach to training machine learning systems by means of a hybrid computer setup i. e. a digital computer tightly coupled with an analog computer. In this example, a reinforcement learning system is trained to balance an inverted pendulum which is simulated on an analog computer, demonstrating a solution to the major challenge of adequately simulating the environment for reinforcement learning.",
